Schema (supabase/schema.sql):
- 8 tables: profiles, accounts, transactions, goals,
  budget_limits, strategies, chat_messages, ai_providers
- Row Level Security on all tables (each user sees only their data)
- Indexes on (user_id, date), (user_id, type), recurring transactions
- auto-updated_at triggers, auto-create profile on auth.users insert
- Constraints: amount > 0, valid enums for type/frequency/provider

Lib (src/lib/):
- supabase.ts: singleton client (anon for browser, service_role for server)
- db.ts: full data access layer with typed functions for every operation
  loadUserState, upsert/delete account, insert/delete transaction,
  upsert/delete goal, upsert budget_limit, upsert/delete strategy,
  save/load/clear chat history, load/save ai_provider config

API routes:
- /api/state: GET loads full state, POST accepts atomic action commands
  (upsert_account, insert_transaction, upsert_goal, etc.) instead of
  overwriting the whole blob — safe for multi-device use
- /api/chat-history: GET/POST/DELETE for persisting conversation to DB

Removes:
- src/lib/mongodb.ts (replaced by supabase.ts + db.ts)
- mongodb npm dependency still in package.json (remove after data migration)

Docs:
- docs/migration-mongodb-to-supabase.md: step-by-step migration guide
- .env.example: updated with Supabase vars + multi-provider AI keys
