From 369fe5fe16018f5004f491649b4923d2b7a8bfde Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dario Pacule <dario@kuhula.finance>
Date: Tue, 23 Jun 2026 04:52:12 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 3/4] feat: wire page.tsx to Supabase + multi-provider AI
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

DB integration:
- usePersistence hook: loads state from DB on mount (localStorage fallback),
  exposes persistAction for atomic DB writes, persistChatMessages for chat history
- saveState now only updates React state + localStorage; DB writes happen
  atomically per tool call via toolCallToPersistAction()
- saveChatHistory persists last 2 messages (new turn) to DB in background
- handleClearAllData calls clearRemoteData() to wipe Supabase rows
- localStorage keys migrated: kuhula_state_v2, kuhula_chat_history,
  kuhula_provider, kuhula_model, kuhula_key_{provider}

Multi-provider AI:
- Provider state: provider (ProviderId) + model + clientApiKey per provider
- handleProviderChange: switches model to provider default, loads saved key
- handleSaveSettings: saves provider/model/key independently per provider
- callChatAPI: sends { provider, model, history as {role,content}[] }
  to unified /api/chat route returning normalized { text, toolCalls, usage }
- handleGeminiResponse → handleAIResponse: handles normalized response,
  calls toolCallToPersistAction for each tool execution
- Settings UI: provider selector + dynamic model list + dynamic key input
  with placeholder and link per provider; FREE badge on providers with
  free-tier models

New files:
- src/lib/ai-providers.ts: 5 providers (Gemini, OpenAI, Anthropic, Groq,
  OpenRouter) with 14 models, free/paid flags, recommended flags
- src/hooks/usePersistence.ts: persistence hook with anonymous userId
